Calls for social distancing and isolation have become the coronavirus battle-cry, and lockdowns are halting cities and towns all over the world (except in Sweden).
Remote working is the new working, and time spent outside the home is down to a bare minimum.
Still, in wealthy countries social distancing is a choice most people can make.
In much of the rest of the world, the concept is an unimaginable luxury.
For the poorest of the world, this epidemic will be yet another catastrophe against which the global order failed to protect them.